08/06/2007
NIS, Serbia -- The commander of KFOR, Lieutenant General Roland Kather, met with Serbian Army Chief of Staff Major General Zdravko Ponos on Thursday (June 7th) and assured him that the security situation in Kosovo is stable and under control.
Meeting in Nis, Kather also stressed that the KFOR troops he leads are working to provide security for all citizens as the status process shifts into the critical phase.
He also rejected media reports suggesting there are terrorist training camps in Kosovo.
(Danas - 08/06/07;
RTK, Telegrafi, RFE - 07/06/07)
